<TITLE> Int'l plastic products fair in Jan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com)The sixth international plastic products fair will be held on Jan 25-28 in Dhaka. Bangladesh Plastic Materials Manufacturers and Exporters' Association president Ferdous Wahed said on Thursday that there would be 350 stalls in the fair to be held at Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre. India, Pakistan, China, Taiwan and Malaysia are among the countries that will take part in the fair. Fair Implementation Committee convener Md Jashim Uddin said the annual turnover of Bangladeshi plastic materials is between Tk 5,000 crore and Tk 6,000 crore and the growth rate is 20 percent. Readymade plastic materials of Tk 600 crore and accessories worth Tk 1,500 crore are being exported, he said. The fair will play a significant role to popularise the plastic materials, Uddin added. The authorities have set the fare of stall at $ 2,000 for the foreign organisations, Tk 30,000 for the association members and Tk 40,000 other Bangladeshi companies. The association and Taiwanese event management organisation Chan Chao are co-organising the fair
